We have that

\begin{align*}
\begin{vmatrix} 1 + a & 1 & 1 \\ 1 & 1 + b & 1 \\ 1 & 1 & 1 + c \end{vmatrix} &= (1+a) (1+b)(1+c)-1(1+c)-1(1+b)-1(1+a) +1\\
&=(1+a)(1+b)(1+c)-1-(a+b+c)-abc\\
&=(1+a+b+c+ab+bc+ca+a+b+c+abc)-1-(a+b+c)-abc\\
&=(ab+bc+ca+abc)+a+b+c.
\end{align*}By Vieta's formulas, we know that $a+b+c =0$, and $ab+bc+ca = p$. Additionally, we have that $-abc = -(-q) = q.$  Therefore, \begin{align*}
(ab+bc+ca+abc)+a+b+c &= p + q.
\end{align*}
